comments: I didn\'t like her at first but she ended up being a great writing teacher (: Her instructions are clear and she\'s fair. Also, she\'s funny. This class isn\'t an "easy A" unless you do your work and you actually try. I would take this professor again (:

I didn\'t like her at first but she ended up being a really great writing teacher. I always thought her instructions were very clear and that she graded fairly. Plus, she\'s funny. I would take this professor again (:

The assignments are not as clear as I would have liked. Her method for grading is very systematic. My interest in the subject was minimal so I didn\'t expect much going in. If you show up and do all of the assignments then you\'ll pass, but don\'t expect an easy "A".

Prof. Wilson is a good, dedicated writing teacher. She wants her students to think clearly and critically and be able to communicate well using academic writing. Jess is firm but fair in her expectations from her students. My writing is definitely improving. Prof. Wilson motivated me to work harder at and to take an honors course for Writing 102.

At first i didnt like Jessica at all because she seemed full of herself but i can honestly say she made me a better writter. she goes a little overboard when correcting papers but dont take it personal... listen to her and accept her criticism! Good teacher!
she never really explained what she wanted. just told you to do it, then ripped it up. also, she rarely shows up for class on time.

Honestly at first I hated her class because she seemed mean but after finishing the class I love her as a teacher I would take her class again. She is very helpful when you need it. She gave a quiz once a week but it was over stuff you read so it was easy. Very understanding teacher
